Subject: Re: [T2] Rust Proofing Tangent

We sandblasted daughter's bus (bad rust pits in roof and rockers and 
front panel) to bare metal, then used DuPont 2 part etching primer to 
seal it, then applied filler that comes from a tube before painting with 
2 part urethane- looks perfect after 7 years.

Joe Average wrote:

> The way it was explained to me a million years ago was that the filler 
> needs to attach directly to the steel metal to adhere properly.
> 
> I was taught to put filler over bare metal to minimize adhesion 
> problems. The filler is only going to stick as well as the paint under 
> it or as well as it sticks to the paint.
